{"title_page": "Valerio Tebaldi", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Valerio Tebaldi\n| image         = \n| full_name     = Valerio Tebaldi\n| nickname      = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1965|7|2}}\n| birth_place   = [[Chiuduno]], [[Italy]]\n| height        = \n| weight        = \n| currentteam   = Retired\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     = \n| amateuryears1 = \n| amateurteam1  = \n| proyears1     = \n| proteam1      = \n| majorwins     = 2 stages Tour de France\n}}\n\n'''Valerio Tebaldi''' (born 2 July 1965) is a former [[Italy|Italian]] professional [[road bicycle racer]]. Tebaldi was born at [[Chiuduno]].  He won a stage in the [[1988 Tour de France]] and in the [[1989 Tour de France]].\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col}}\n;1988\n:[[1988 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::Winner stage 7\n;1989\n:[[1989 Tour de France|Tour de France]]:\n::Winner stage 12\n{{div col end}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Cycling Archives|7124}}\n*{{Tour de France results|4932|archive=20080612181810}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tebaldi, Valerio}}\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian Tour de France stage winners]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Bergamo]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Lombardy]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n\n\n{{Italy-cycling-bio-1960s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Valerio Tebaldi\n| image         = \n| full_name     = Valerio Tebaldi\n| nickname      = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1965|7|2}}\n| birth_place   = [[Chiuduno]], [[Italy]]\n| height        = \n| weight        = \n| currentteam   = Retired\n| discipline    = Road\n| role          = Rider\n| ridertype     = \n| amateuryears1 = \n| amateurteam1  = \n| proyears1     = \n| proteam1      = \n| majorwins     = 